  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <h3>Effective Date: September 17, 2013</h3>
  <div>
    <p>By using EarDish you agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy and the Terms and Conditions.  This Privacy Policy explains how we protect your privacy. It also sets forth the type of information we collect and what we do with it.</p>

    <h2>1. The Type of Information We Collect</h2>

    <p>We do not share your personally identifiable information, such as your name and email addresses, with any third parties unless done so for the purpose of processing payments for earnings you have accrued and/or for reasonable legal reasons as set forth below.</p> 

    <p>There are two types of information that we collect.  We collect aggregated, anonymous information. We also collect your personal information when you join our site as a member. Such personal information includes your name, your location such as your Zip Code or Postal Code, your mailing address, gender, age, email address and username and password.  We need this information in order to conduct business with our artists, fans and other members.</p>

    <h2>2. Information Gathered Through Technologies</h2>

    <p>We collect non-personally identifiable information through technologies such as cookies, Flash cookies and Web beacons as you use our site, tools and services. You may disable cookies in your browser by following the instructions in your Browser’s user guide or preference settings. However, if you disable your cookies our Site may not operate properly for you.</p>

    <p>As is standard practice on many corporate websites, we also log non-personally-identifiable information including IP address, profile information, aggregate user data, and browser type, from members to the site. This data is used to improve the website services, to analyze trends, to administer the site, to track users' movements around the site and to gather demographic information about our user base as a whole. We will not use the information collected to market directly to that person. However, this non-personally-identifiable information may be shared with third-parties, to provide more relevant services and advertisements to our members and User IP addresses are recorded for security and monitoring purposes.</p>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>

    <p>We will use your personal information to contact you for general business purposes and or to respond to a request you have made such as to answer a question or help you with a service related complaint.</p>

    <p>We may also collect information for market research purposes to gain a better understanding of our customers and thus provide more valuable service. We also collect information regarding customer activities on our website, and on related websites. This helps us to determine how best to provide useful information to customers and to understand which parts of our websites and Internet services are of most interest to them.</p>

    <p>In cases where you use a mobile device to access our sites or use or applications, we may receive information about the location of your device. We may use this information to develop, deliver, and improve our products, services, and other offerings.</p>

    <p>We uses cookies to store visitors' preferences and to record session information, for purposes including:</p>

    <p>1) Ensuring that visitors are not repeatedly offered the same advertisements, to customize newsletter, advertising, and Web page content based on browser type and user profile information;</p>

    <p>2) To help track usage to help us understand which parts of our website are the most popular, where our visitors are going, and how much time they spend there;</p>

    <p>3) To make usage of our website even more rewarding as well as to study the effectiveness of our customer communications, and</p>

    <p>4) To customize each visitor's experience and provide greater convenience.</p>

    <h2>4. Sharing Your Information with Other Companies</h2>

    <p>Except as otherwise described in this Privacy Policy, We will not disclose personal information to any third party unless believe that disclosure is necessary:</p>

    <p>1) To conform to legal requirements or to respond to a subpoena, search warrant or other legal process received by EarDish, whether or not a response is required by applicable law;</p>

    <p>2) To enforce the EarDish Terms and Conditions or to protect our rights; or</p>

    <p>3) To protect the safety of members of the public and of the service. We reserve the right to transfer personal information to a successor in interest that acquires rights to that information as a result of the sale of EarDish or substantially all of its assets to that successor in interest.</p>

    <h2>5. Strategic Relationship – Privacy Policy Obligations</h2>

    <p>We take your privacy very seriously. We do not sell or rent your contact information to other marketers. There are also times when it may be advantageous for we to make certain personal information about you available to companies that we have a strategic relationship with or that perform work for us to provide products and services to you on our behalf, such as providing non-personally identifiable information such as aggregated demographics for promotional and or advertising purposes.</p>

    <p>These companies may help us process information, deliver products to you, manage and enhance customer data, provide customer service, assess your interest in our products and services, or conduct customer research or satisfaction surveys.</p>

    <p>These companies are also obligated to protect your personal information in accordance with our privacy policies. Without such information being made available, it would be difficult for you to receive customer service, provide us feedback to improve our products and services, or access certain services, offers, and content on the EarDish website.</p>

    <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>

    <p>Our Terms of Service require that users must be at least 13 years of age to use our Site. EarDish is not directed to children under the age of 13. We operate our site in compliance with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act of 1998, and do not permit registration by, and will not knowingly collect or use personally identifiable information from, anyone under 13 years of age. This requirement is clearly posted during the registration process and subject to our Terms of Service.</p>

    <h2>7. Data Security and Integrity</h2>

    <p>The security, integrity and confidentiality of your information are of great concern to us. Accordingly, we have implemented security measures that are designed to protect member and user information from unauthorized access, disclosure, use and modification. We review our security procedures from time to time to consider the implementation of appropriate new technology and related security procedures. Please be aware though that, despite our best efforts, no security measures are 100% foolproof.  No Website or data can ever be maintained with a guarantee of 100% security against loss or access by unauthorized third parties.</p>

    <p>We take precautions to insure that account information is kept private. Additionally, we use reasonable measures such as encryption to protect private information that is stored within our database against loss, theft, and misuse, as well as unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction, and we restrict access to such private information to those employees who need access to perform their job functions, such as our customer service personnel and technical staff. Please note that we cannot 100% guarantee the security of all account information. Unauthorized entry or use, hardware or software failure, and other factors may compromise the security of member information at any time. Users are urged to also take precautions to protect their personal data by changing passwords often using a combination of letters and numbers, and using a secure web browser.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>

    <p>We reserve the right to modify, change or alter this Privacy Policy at anytime. Additionally, unless explicitly stated otherwise, any current, updated and new products and services ("Products and Services"), including the addition of new properties shall be subject to this Privacy Policy, as well as the General Terms and Conditions of Use ("Terms and Conditions").</p>

    <p>However, we reserve the right to post a 30-day notice, prior to any substantial changes to our Privacy Policy in order to allow for member review of any substantial changes, prior to implementation.</p>

    <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>

    <p>EarDish.com, advertisers and users, may provide links to third party sites. In the event that you allow sharing of your personal information with third-party sites or platforms, such as social networking sites, the information received by the other company becomes subject to the other company's privacy practices.</p>

    <p>We are not responsible for the Privacy Policies of any third party Site. Please carefully review the Privacy Polices of any such third party sites before you use the site you have been referred to.</p>

    <h2>10. Notice to California Residents:</h2>

    <p>If you are a California resident, California Civil Code Section 1798.83 permits you to request information regarding the disclosure of your personal information by EarDish Corporation. With respect EarDish Corporation, this privacy policy applies only to user activities within the State of California. To make such a request, please send write us:</p>

    <p>CA Privacy Policy<br/>
